There is currently a hard-coded error for multi-PART Abaqus files in the libmesh AbaqusIO reader:
          // 0.) Look for the "*Part" section
          if (upper.find("*PART") == static_cast<std::string::size_type>(0))
            {
              libmesh_error_msg_if
                (_already_seen_part,
                 "We currently don't support reading Abaqus files with multiple PART sections");

              _already_seen_part = true;
            }

but I think this is mainly due to not having a good test case in the past to develop the reader from, rather than any fundamental reason why they could not be supported.
I don't know of any current plans to add support for this type of file.
